derivation.yuyuan_name: from flap (in the dialect sense 'toss a pancake') + jack

entry.def: Flapjacks are thick biscuits made from oats, butter, and syrup.
Flapjacks are thin, flat, circular pieces of cooked batter made of milk, flour, and eggs. Flapjacks are usually rolled up or folded and eaten hot with a sweet or savoury filling.

means.word_mean: 1. a flat cake of thin batter fried on both sides on a griddle
